params.name: do_affine_transform
params.description: Whether to apply an affine transformation to the input images.

params.name: size
params.type: Dict[str, int] optional, defaults to {"height" -- 256, "width": 192}):Resolution of the image after affine_transform is applied. Only has an effect if do_affine_transform is set to True. Canbe overriden by size in the preprocess method.

params.name: do_rescale
params.description: Whether or not to apply the scaling factor (to make pixel values floats between 0. and 1.).

params.name: rescale_factor
params.description: Scale factor to use if rescaling the image. Can be overriden by rescale_factor in the preprocessmethod.

params.name: do_normalize
params.description: Whether or not to normalize the input with mean and standard deviation.

params.name: image_mean
params.description: The sequence of means for each channel, to be used when normalizing images.

params.name: image_std
params.description: The sequence of standard deviations for each channel, to be used when normalizing images.
